The global military vetronics market is segmented based on system, vehicle type, and component. In terms of the system, the market is further categorized into vehicle protection system, power distribution system, vehicle information system, and others. The vehicle protection system segment is expected to witness significant growth due to the increasing focus on enhancing the safety and security features of military vehicles. The power distribution system segment is also anticipated to grow as it plays a crucial role in efficiently distributing power across various components of the vehicle. Moreover, the vehicle information system segment is likely to expand with advancements in technology enabling better communication and coordination in military operations. When it comes to vehicle type, the market covers main battle tanks, light protected vehicles, amphibious armored vehicles, and unmanned ground vehicles. Main battle tanks are projected to dominate the market owing to their widespread use in modern warfare scenarios. The component segment is divided into hardware and software, where hardware is expected to hold a larger market share due to the continuous advancements in technology.

